  "texts": [
    "In contrast, models like ChatGPT-3.5 Turbo and Qianwen-14B -Base showed relatively lower scores, 56.25% and 42.86%, respectively.",
    "The Composite Medical Content (CMC) dataset, which assesses the models' understanding of medical knowledge specifically in the Chinese context, saw MediGuide-14B performing the best with a score of 77.56%.",
    "ChatGPT-4 and Lingyi Zhihui also showed strong results with scores above 73%.",
    "highlighted the effectiveness of ChatGPT-4 and MediGuide-14B, which scored 74.58% and 75.41%, respectively, demonstrating their robustness in handling questions related to the Chinese Medical Licensing Examination.",
    "Lower-tier models, such as LLaMA 2-13B, had notably weaker performance, indicating possible challenges in their language-specific medical knowledge."
  ]
}